SIMPLE: adaw
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Adaw
<hw>A*daw"</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[Cf. OE.
<ets>adawe</ets> of dawe, AS. <ets>of dagum</ets> from days, <it>i.
e.</it>, from life, out of life.]</ety> <def>To subdue; to daunt.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The sight whereof did greatly him <qex>adaw</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adaw</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Adaw
<hw>A*daw"</hw>, <pos>v. t. & i.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>adawen</ets> to
wake; pref. <ets>a-</ets> (cf. Goth. <ets>us</ets>-, Ger.
<ets>er</ets>-) + <ets>dawen</ets>, <ets>dagon</ets>, to dawn. See
<er>Daw</er>.]</ety> <def>To awaken; to arouse.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>A man that waketh of his sleep⟦br⟧
He may not suddenly well taken keep⟦br⟧
Upon a thing, ne seen it parfitly⟦br⟧
Till that he be <qex>adawed</qex> verily.</q>
<rj><qau>Chaucer.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Adays</ent>⟦br⟧
